<subSubSection id="C301F9D83567FFB945984624331EFDF9" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA4AA533567FFB945984624331EFDF9" blockId="99.[151,1437,259,610]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="B96F76413567FFB945984624372CFE6C" bold="true" box="[199,367,367,396]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
Diagnosis (
<specimenCount id="9D1D61DA3567FFB94414463A3723FE6C" box="[331,352,369,396]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
).
</emphasis>
An anophthalmic hypogean 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03567FFB947EF46243560FE69" authorityName="Rayi L. Koch" authorityYear="1873" box="[688,803,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F76413567FFB947EF46243560FE69" box="[688,803,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Chthonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that differs from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03567FFB9419A46243317FE69" baseAuthorityName="Hermann" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1221,1364,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ischnocheles">
<emphasis id="B96F76413567FFB9419A46243317FE69" box="[1221,1364,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">ischnocheles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the following combination of characters: anterior margin of carapace without preocular microsetae; posterior margin of carapace with 2 macrosetae and 1 or 2 lateral microsetae; tergites I–II with 2 setae; chelicerae without lateral microsetae; chela 8.0 times as long as deep; chela length 
<quantity id="4CE307B63567FFB9463046903594FE16" box="[879,983,475,502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.52" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="1.52">1.52 mm</quantity>
; movable chelal finger length 
<quantity id="4CE307B63567FFB9406F469033DBFE16" box="[1328,1432,475,502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="1.08">1.08 mm</quantity>
; chelal fingers with contiguous teeth; fixed chelal finger with 86 teeth; ratio of pedipalpal femur/carapace 1.9.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
