<typeStatus id="54A014F13567FFB9464B429D353AFA10" box="[788,889,1494,1520]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">holotype</typeStatus>
, Dr Paolo Marcia (University of Sassari), in recognition of his contribution to the knowledge of the subterranean fauna of 
<collectingRegion id="49DF64B13567FFB9468542B13278F9F4" box="[986,1083,1530,1556]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C301F9D83567FFBF459841553418FD2D" lastPageId="101" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA4AA533567FFBF4598415534CAFD81" blockId="99.[151,1437,1494,2025]" lastBlockId="101.[151,1437,150,1113]" lastPageId="101" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="B96F76413567FFB94598415534E1F9D8" bold="true" box="[199,674,1566,1595]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
Description of adults (
<specimenCount id="9D1D61DA3567FFB94484416B37B2F9DB" box="[475,497,1568,1595]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
; 
<specimenCount id="9D1D61DA3567FFB9475C416B345BF9DB" box="[515,536,1568,1595]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
unknown).
</emphasis>
Highly specialized troglomorphic facies; integument slightly pigmented, carapace, tergites, chelicerae and pedipalps pale brown; weak hispid granulation on cheliceral palm. Carapace (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63567FFB94584412D377FF960" box="[219,316,1638,1664]" captionStart="FIGURES 312–315" captionStartId="99.[151,264,1388,1412]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,638,1360]" captionTargetId="figure-154@99.[151,1436,633,1364]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 312–315. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 312, anterior margin of carapace; 313, carapace; 314, right chelicera; 315, right chelal hand, dorsal view." pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 313</figureCitation>
) 0.95 times longer than broad, trapezoidal, constricted posteriorly; anterior margin denticulate between median macrosetae, with a prominent epistome (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63567FFB9465541C1352EF944" box="[778,877,1674,1700]" captionStart="FIGURES 312–315" captionStartId="99.[151,264,1388,1412]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,638,1360]" captionTargetId="figure-154@99.[151,1436,633,1364]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 312–315. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 312, anterior margin of carapace; 313, carapace; 314, right chelicera; 315, right chelal hand, dorsal view." pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 312</figureCitation>
); ocular area as in fig. 313, no eyes or eye-spots; chaetotaxy 4:6:4:2:m 
<quantity id="4CE307B63567FFB944DF41E53780F929" box="[384,451,1710,1737]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="2.0">2mm</quantity>
(21), setae long and thin, length of anteromedian macrosetae 
<quantity id="4CE307B63567FFB941DA41E532ACF929" box="[1157,1263,1710,1737]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.18">0.18 mm</quantity>
. Chaetotaxy of tergites 2:2:4:4:6:6:6:6:1T2T1:4:1T2T1:0. Chaetotaxy of sternites 9:(3)11(3):(2)6(2):8:6:6:6:6:2T2T2:0:2; genital opening flanked by 12 setae on each side, partly scattered. Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63567FFB946E241BD325DF8F0" box="[957,1054,1782,1808]" captionStart="FIGURES 312–315" captionStartId="99.[151,264,1388,1412]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,638,1360]" captionTargetId="figure-154@99.[151,1436,633,1364]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 312–315. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 312, anterior margin of carapace; 313, carapace; 314, right chelicera; 315, right chelal hand, dorsal view." pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 314</figureCitation>
) 2.5 times as long as broad, palm with 6 setae, without lateral microsetae; fixed finger with 2 distal large teeth followed by 13 small teeth proximally increasingly reduced; movable finger with an isolated subapical tooth (
<emphasis id="B96F76413567FFB946EF40753585F8B8" box="[944,966,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">di</emphasis>
) at level with the spinneret, followed by a large tooth and 12 teeth proximally reduced in size; 
<emphasis id="B96F76413567FFB9478B402834AEF89C" box="[724,749,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">gs</emphasis>
ratio 0.61; spinneret weakly raised, large and rounded; rallum with 11 blades; serrulae interior and exterior with 14 and 15 blades respectively. Coxal setae: pedipalp 5 (including 2 on manducatory process), I 3 + 3 marginal microsetae, II 4 and 5, III 6, IV 7; coxa II with 10 and 12 coxal spines, coxa III with 5 and 7 coxal spines; intercoxal tubercle bisetose. Pedipalp: femur 7.9 times as long as broad, femoral chaetotaxy 3:6:2:5:1; chela (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63561FFBF448D47DC3472FF52" box="[466,561,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 316–319" captionStartId="100.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[330,1256,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-32@100.[329,1259,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURES 316–319. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 316, right chela, antiaxial view; 317, detail of dentition at the right chelal fingers tip, antiaxial view; 318, detail of fingers at level of trichobothria est-it and st-t, antiaxial view; 319, detail of fingers at level of trichobothrium sb, antiaxial view." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 316</figureCitation>
) 8.0 times as long as deep; hand of chela 2.35 times as long as deep, with parallel sides in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63561FFBF44FC47F03447FF35" box="[419,516,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 312–315" captionStartId="99.[151,264,1388,1412]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,638,1360]" captionTargetId="figure-154@99.[151,1436,633,1364]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 312–315. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 312, anterior margin of carapace; 313, carapace; 314, right chelicera; 315, right chelal hand, dorsal view." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Fig. 315</figureCitation>
); fixed chelal finger with 86 contiguous teeth: 63 distal teeth cuspidate and slightly inclined backwards, 15 low and rounded teeth increasingly reduced towards trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF41C7479432F2FF19" box="[1176,1201,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">sb</emphasis>
and 8 proximal teeth recognizable only by the presence of dental canal (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63561FFBF478946483534FEFD" box="[726,887,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 316–319" captionStartId="100.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[330,1256,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-32@100.[329,1259,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURES 316–319. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 316, right chela, antiaxial view; 317, detail of dentition at the right chelal fingers tip, antiaxial view; 318, detail of fingers at level of trichobothria est-it and st-t, antiaxial view; 319, detail of fingers at level of trichobothrium sb, antiaxial view." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Figs 317–319</figureCitation>
), all teeth with dental canal; fixed finger at level of 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF45E9466C36ADFEA0" box="[182,238,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">est-it</emphasis>
with 8 teeth occupying 
<quantity id="4CE307B63561FFBF475F466C341AFEA1" box="[512,601,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
, distance between successive apices 
<quantity id="4CE307B63561FFBF46A5466D323EFEA1" box="[1018,1149,294,321]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="0.0115">0.0115 mm</quantity>
; tip of fixed chelal finger with apical sensilla 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4429460037CFFE85" box="[374,396,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">af</emphasis>
<subScript id="179FA8163561FFBF44CB461637EAFE8B" attach="right" box="[404,425,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF44CB461637E2FE8B" box="[404,417,349,363]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">1-</emphasis>
2
</subScript>
, distal paraxial seta gradually curved and thin; movable chelal finger with 75 teeth: distal half of the finger with 42 more widely spaced teeth, slightly scalene triangle-shaped, reclined and apically pointed; proximal half of the finger with 33 teeth that are apically rounded and increasingly reduced towards finger base, reaching back near 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF442946FC37C7FE31" box="[374,388,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">b</emphasis>
(between 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF44A346FC3456FE31" box="[508,533,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">sb</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF471146FC341FFE31" box="[590,604,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">b</emphasis>
they are mainly recognizable only by the presence of dental canal) (
<figureCitation id="1320B6D63561FFBF403546FC36BDFE15" captionStart="FIGURES 316–319" captionStartId="100.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[330,1256,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-32@100.[329,1259,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURES 316–319. Chthonius marciai n. sp., male holotype. 316, right chela, antiaxial view; 317, detail of dentition at the right chelal fingers tip, antiaxial view; 318, detail of fingers at level of trichobothria est-it and st-t, antiaxial view; 319, detail of fingers at level of trichobothrium sb, antiaxial view." pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Figs 317–319</figureCitation>
); movable finger at level of 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF47664690341EFE14" box="[569,605,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">st-t</emphasis>
with 7 teeth occupying 
<quantity id="4CE307B63561FFBF463646903582FE15" box="[873,961,475,501]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
, distance between successive apices 
<quantity id="4CE307B63561FFBF400246903685FDF9" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" unit="mm" value="0.014">0.014 mm</quantity>
; coupled sensilla 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF44D446B437E6FDF8" box="[395,421,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">pc</emphasis>
just distad of 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF471C46B4341FFDF9" box="[579,604,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">sb</emphasis>
; tip of movable chelal finger with apical sensilla 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF41DB46B432E5FDF8" box="[1156,1190,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">am</emphasis>
<subScript id="179FA8163561FFBF41F2455A3281FDFF" attach="right" box="[1197,1218,529,543]" fontSize="6" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF41F2455A32F9FDFF" box="[1197,1210,529,543]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">1-</emphasis>
2
</subScript>
; trichobothria as in fig. 316; ratio 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4467456837E6FDDD" box="[312,421,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">sb -st/sb -b</emphasis>
= 1.6; ratio of movable finger/hand of chela 2.4; ratio of pedipalpal femur/movable finger 0.95; ratio of pedipalpal femur/carapace 1.9.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF64FADB3560FFBE45C840DC34E6F818" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" startId="100.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[330,1256,181,1915]" targetPageId="100">
<paragraph id="8BA4AA533560FFBE45C840DC34E6F818" blockId="100.[151,1436,1943,2040]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis id="B96F76413560FFBE45C840DC372DF84F" bold="true" box="[151,366,1943,1967]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">FIGURES 316–319.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03560FFBE442940D33477F84F" authority="Gardini, 2021" authorityName="Gardini" authorityYear="2021" box="[374,564,1944,1968]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marciai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96F76413560FFBE442940D33477F84F" box="[374,564,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Chthonius marciai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96F76413560FFBE476440D33435F850" bold="true" box="[571,630,1944,1968]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25CCB3A3560FFBE476440D33435F850" box="[571,630,1944,1968]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype. 316, right chela, antiaxial view; 317, detail of dentition at the right chelal fingers tip, antiaxial view; 318, detail of fingers at level of trichobothria 
<emphasis id="B96F76413560FFBE46B440F7325DF833" box="[1003,1054,1980,2003]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">est-it</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B96F76413560FFBE411140F7322DF833" box="[1102,1134,1980,2003]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">st-t</emphasis>
, antiaxial view; 319, detail of fingers at level of trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="B96F76413560FFBE44B140AB3446F818" box="[494,517,2016,2040]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">sb</emphasis>
, antiaxial view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA4AA533561FFBF459845203418FD2D" blockId="101.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Measurements (in mm). Body length 1.5 (opisthosoma moderately shrunk). Carapace 0.54 × 0.57 (0.56 anteriorly). Chelicerae 0.64 × 0.25; movable finger length 0.33. Pedipalp: femur 1.03 × 0.13; chela 1.52 × 0.19; hand length 0.45; movable finger length 1.08.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C301F9D83561FFBF4598459C379AFBB9" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4AA533561FFBF4598459C3251FC29" blockId="101.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4598459C3778FD11" bold="true" box="[199,315,727,753]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the western Mediterranean species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03561FFBF4617459C35F8FD11" authorityName="Rayi L. Koch" authorityYear="1873" box="[840,955,727,753]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4617459C35F8FD11" box="[840,955,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Chthonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with contiguous chelal teeth, none has the combination of characters shown by 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03561FFBF476345B034F7FCF4" authority="Gardini, 2021" authorityName="Gardini" authorityYear="2021" box="[572,692,763,789]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marciai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF476345B034F7FCF4" box="[572,692,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">C. marciai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25CCB3A3561FFBF47E245B034BEFCF5" box="[701,765,763,789]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: anterior margin of carapace without preocular microsetae, posterior margin of carapace with 2 macrosetae and 1 or 2 lateral microsetae, tergites I–II each with 2 setae and chelicerae without lateral microsetae. Among the species with troglomorphic facies, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03561FFBF4177440832BBFCBC" authorityName="Gardini" authorityYear="2021" box="[1064,1272,835,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marciai">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4177440832BBFCBC" box="[1064,1272,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Chthonius marciai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comparable to 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF45EB442C368DFC61" box="[180,206,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">C.</emphasis>
sp. cf 
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4447442C373CFC61" box="[280,383,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">lucifugus</emphasis>
Mahnert, 1977 from the Rendez-vous de chasse Cave (Hérault, 
<collectingCountry id="F30CEAC33561FFBF4110442C32DEFC61" box="[1103,1181,871,897]" name="France" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">France</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AD7A23561FFBF41EC442C330BFC61" author="Leclerc, P." box="[1203,1352,871,897]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="11 - 19" refId="ref120655" refString="Leclerc, P. (1983) Les Chthoniidae de la grotte du Rendez-vous de Chasse (Herault) (Arachnides, Pseudoscorpions). Bulletin de la Societe d'Etude des Sciences naturelles de Beziers, New Series, 9 (50), 11 - 19." type="journal article" year="1983">Leclerc 1983</bibRefCitation>
) which has no preocular microsetae, tergites I–II with 2 and 4 setae and chelicerae without lateral microsetae, but the latter has 2 macrosetae on the posterior margin of carapace and no lateral microsetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4AA533561FFBF45984498379AFBB9" blockId="101.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03561FFBF4598449837D4FC0C" authorityName="Gardini" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,407,979,1005]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marciai">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF4598449837D4FC0C" box="[199,407,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Chthonius marciai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be related to the halophilic 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BD1D03561FFBF464C449835CEFC0D" authorityName="Kew" authorityYear="1916" box="[787,909,979,1005]" class="Arachnida" family="Chthoniidae" genus="Chthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pseudoscorpiones" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halberti">
<emphasis id="B96F76413561FFBF464C449835CEFC0D" box="[787,909,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">C. halberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a Mediterranean–Atlantic species also present in 
<collectingRegion id="49DF64B13561FFBF45E944BC3750FBF1" box="[182,275,1015,1041]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
that has no preocular microsetae, the posterior margin of carapace with a variable number of setae (5 to 8), the chelicerae without lateral microsetae, but tergites I–II with 4 or more setae. Evident adaptive characters differentiate the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
